        <list id="id8871376" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-roman" mark-prefix="(" mark-suffix=")">
          <item>The dry regions</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id8726190">The major part of our country is dry. Convection rain in the form of isolated thunderstorms does bring rain. Because it is so dry, there is little vegetation, and erosion in these areas is therefore a big problem.</para>
        <para id="id1164562233527">In the half-dry regions like the Karoo the vegetation consists of low, grey karoo shrubs like guarri and rhenoster bush and hardy grasses. In the drier areas along the west coast sparsely distributed succulents occur. These succulents have thick, fleshy leaves to store water. Some of them can survive for years without water.</para>
      </section>
